    "text": [
        "Majority of people believe that a foreign language is solely learnt with the purpose of visiting other countries or business goals, while, there is an opposite opinion that the mentioned goals are not the absolute reason to learn another language. In this regard I am going to discuss both views and elaborate on my reasons to concur with the second opinion.",
        "A foreign language aquisition has been Stryotepicaly believed to be only for people who aim to spend their vacation abroad or their job requires international interactios, while these types of reasons have Bold because of the two type of mentioned motives are the most Common reasons to learn a foriegn language, there are a great number of people who only learn foreign languages for enjoyment or there are scientific porpuses behind their decisions to do so. For example a great number of Korean Language learners in my country state that their goal is to learn this language only for the pleasure of watching korean movies.",
        "It is worth mentioning that a significant number of people learn other languages to study other cultures and linguistic structure of other languages. In this regard, nowadays, a great proportion of diffrent foreign languages have been established in universities and this trend is developing among world universities day by day. For instance the department of Japanese language and literature has been recently commenced its activity in my university, although, the classes are small and facilities like books and Learning materials are not sufficient due to been newly stablished, but the number of applicants for this major is incridibaly higher than expections and more than half of these people only intend to learn this language because they love Japan and its culture.",
        "In drawing to a close, business and travel are not the only reasons to aquire a foreign languages but also there are a great number of people who follow this path only for their love toward a culture And language of a nation,"
